    "readme_content": "---\nlibrary_name: transformers\ntags:\n - transformers.js\n - tokenizers\n---\n\n# GPT-3.5-turbo-16k Tokenizer\n\nA \ud83e\udd17-compatible version of the **GPT-3.5-turbo-16k tokenizer** (adapted from [openai/tiktoken](https://github.com/openai/tiktoken)). This means it can be used with Hugging Face libraries including [Transformers](https://github.com/huggingface/transformers), [Tokenizers](https://github.com/huggingface/tokenizers), and [Transformers.js](https://github.com/xenova/transformers.js).\n\n## Example usage:\n\n### Transformers/Tokenizers\n```py\nfrom transformers import GPT2TokenizerFast\n\ntokenizer = GPT2TokenizerFast.from_pretrained('Xenova/gpt-3.5-turbo-16k')\nassert tokenizer.encode('hello world') == [15339, 1917]\n```\n\n### Transformers.js\n```js\nimport { AutoTokenizer } from '@xenova/transformers';\n\nconst tokenizer = await AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained('Xenova/gpt-3.5-turbo-16k');\nconst tokens = tokenizer.encode('hello world'); // [15339, 1917]\n```\n",
